(56875, 49, 3, 'bag1|LogoFashion|White|Sample Bag|One of the first things you are required to do when adding a new product to your catalog is to specify the product type. Magento’s product catalog is based upon six product types, which are divided into two groups which can be called “Simple” and “Complex.” In this case, the word “complex” conveys the meaning of compound, or one-to-many. A Simple product is a physical item with a single SKU. Simple products have a variety of pricing and input controls, which makes it possible to sell many variations of a product. Simple products can be used in association with Bundle, Grouped and Configurable Products. Here are some selected options of Magento catalog management: Inventory Management with Backordered items Simple, Configurable (e.g. size, color, etc.), Bundled and Grouped Products Downloadable/Digital Products, Virtual Products Customer Personalized Products - upload text for embroidery, monogramming, etc. Create Store-specific attributes on the fly Tax Rates per location, customer group and product type Advanced Pricing Rules and support for Special Prices Attribute Sets for quick product creation of different item types Media Manager with automatic image resizing and watermarking Search Results rewrites and redirects Approve, Edit and Delete Product Reviews and Tags RSS feed for Low Inventory Alerts Batch Import and Export of catalog Batch Updates to products in admin panel|There are many different product types in Magento. The Simple Product type should be used for that generally have a single configuration (one-size-fits-all). Every product can also have additional options.|75.95|1'),
